genetics

Class ASCIIChromosome

  • java.lang.Object
    • genetics.ASCIIChromosome
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IChromosome

    public class ASCIIChromosome
extends java.lang.Object
implements IChromosome
    This class implements the IChromosome-interface. An ASCIIChromosome is represented by a gene-string that consists of a subset of the ASCII characters. The randomLetter-method basically determines which subset of the ASCII characters is being used.
    Author:
    Jakob Dhondt
